The paper discusses the sociopolitical issues surrounding the use of AI in society, particularly in relation to race and gender biases. This suggests that it could fall under the category of "Computers and Society" (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning and natural language processing, which are common topics in the categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses biases in decision-making tools, which could fall under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) or "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
